title: Mourning Her Brave
description: Brush, George de Forrest - Mourning Her Brave - oil on panel.  Image of an American Indian woman standing on a snowy cliff, barefoot.  Above her lies the wrapped body of her deceased mate, and birds fly in the hazy gray sky.
